Package org.planit.metroscan.input

Class MetroScan

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.planit.metroscan.input.MetroScan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, InputBuilderListener
    public class MetroScan
extends Object
implements InputBuilderListener
    MetroScan specific input reader which takes the MetroScan GeoJSON format and converts it into the internal memory model

        private Map<Integer,​Node> parsedNodes
        Tracks parsed node locations to avoid registering duplicates as nodes are not separately parsed but implicit components of links. Note, directPosition is not Comparable, so hashCode is used instead to identify them uniquely.

      • parseMetroscanLinkSegments

        private void parseMetroscanLinkSegments​(@Nonnull
                                        PhysicalNetwork network,
                                        @Nonnull
                                        Link theLink,
                                        @Nonnull
                                        SimpleFeature linkFeature)
                                 throws PlanItException
        Parse any link segments for the passed in link
        Parameters:
        network - the physical network object to store network details
        theLink - link to place the segments on
        linkFeature - link feature object to extract the segment data from
        Throws:
        PlanItException - thrown if there is an error IMPORTANT ASSUMPTION ******* We are using the "gid" property in the network input file to get the network ID of the A NODE. The gid value should match with the value of a connectoid property in TAZ input file.
